armers, so much so that his popularity rivaled that of Gandhi himself. Even in prison, Bhagat made headline news when he and other prisoners undertook a 63 day fast unto death to improve the conditions of Indian freedom-fighter prisoners. Then the British re-opened the Saunders' murder case, which led to death sentences being imposed on Bhagat, Shivram, and Sukhdev. The entire nation rose up in protest, including the Congress party - with the ball being in Gandhi's court - for he was due to sign the Irwing Pact, and Indians hoped that he would use this as a bargaining chip to save the lives of the heroic trio. Will Gandhi rise up to the occasion and save the trio - so that they could pave the way for a modern and independent India, not just a country ruled by the British with a dominant status - an India free of communal hatred, injustice, corruption, and fundamentalism, or will Gandhi end up disappointing Bhagat all over again?, awards=10 wins & 3 nominations., lastupdated=2015-08-15 00:01:50.553000000, type=movie, languages=[Hindi, English, Bengali, Panjabi], directors=[Rajkumar Santoshi], writers=[Ranjit Kapoor (additional dialogue), Piyush Mishra (Hindi dialogue), Anjum Rajabali (English dialogue), Anjum Rajabali (screenplay), Rajkumar Santoshi (additional dialogue)], imdb=Document{{rating=8.1, votes=5664, id=319736}}, countries=[India], rated=NOT RATED, genres=[Biography, Drama, History], tomatoes=Document{{viewer=Document{{rating=4.0, numReviews=341, meter=85}}, dvd=Tue Jan 06 01:00:00 CET 2004, lastUpdated=Fri Aug 14 20:31:54 CEST 2015}}}}
