s The Phantom, who in 1946 attacked five couples parked on lovers' lanes. This unsolved crime that has created its own unique urban legend in Texarkana, perpetuated by a town that refuses to forget. The Killer Clown: In Chicago, the filmmakers investigate the "phantom clown" scares that have been spontaneously occurring since the 1980s. In cities across the globe, clowns have been spotted in vans trying to snatch children. Is this just a case of hysteria, manifested by fears of coulrophobia (the fear of clowns), or is there something much more serious at work? Chicago's creepy clown past, from John Wayne Gacy to Bozo, is explored in an attempt to answer the question of how clowns became so evil, and why they continue to haunt our nightmares., lastupdated=2015-08-29 00:10:07.343000000, type=movie, languages=[English], directors=[Joshua Zeman], writers=[Joshua Zeman], imdb=Document{{rating=6.4, votes=1155, id=3449040}}, countries=[USA], genres=[Documentary, Crime, History]}}
